http://www.dt.fee.unicamp.br/~tiago/smsspamcollection/ 

There are two requirements.txt file. One is for the notebook ("nb_requirements"),
 the other is for the script ("requirements").
 This is so the docker container uses only the packages needed for the API.

When running the container you may need to specify the port, as you may not be able to connect to the api site otherwise.
try: docker run -p 8000:8000 [image_name]

 

